{{Quote|We freely admit that the Alliance of Free Planets is merely an interim measure, a stepping stone on the path to the restoration of the ideals of a bygone day&hellip;:<br />&hellip; the first step towards a New Republic.|Excerpt from [[Declaration of the Alliance of Free Planets]]|<ref name="TABSB" />}}
The '''Alliance of Free Planets''' was the interim government established in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] as part of its formal transition into the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].

==History==
{{Quote|We are no longer the Rebel Alliance. United, we are quite literally, an Alliance of Free Planets. And so shall we remain until the Republic can be restored.|Mon Mothma|<ref name="TAB Sourcebook">''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''</ref>}}
The Alliance of Free Planets existed only one month before the formal creation of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], yet made some important steps forward for the fledgling government. The Alliance of Free Planets, was [[Declaration of the Alliance of Free Planets|formed]] one week after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], in the aftermath of the [[Bakura Incident]].<ref name="TABSB" /> The rebels defeated the [[Ssi-ruu]]k at [[Bakura/Legends|Bakura]], for the first time fighting alongside [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces against a common foe. Though, the temporary alliance was fragile and marred with suspicion on both sides, it was an important symbolic move for the Alliance.<ref name="TAB">''[[The Truce at Bakura]]''</ref>

[[File:ConferenceGroup.jpg|thumb|left|250px|A group of delegates listen to [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]].]]

To cement the gains made at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], the [[First Conference of Free Peoples]]<ref name="MC90" /> was convened to tackle many of the issues relating to internal governance and the formation of a more permanent body; the New Republic.<ref name="TABSB" />

In this intervening period, the Alliance also had to contend with other hostile forces threatening to tear it apart. Grumblings from a number of member worlds over the leadership style led to a [[Skirmish on Kabray|conference on Kabray]], resolved by the swift action of [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] and her [[Zeltron/Legends|Zeltron]] aides.<ref name="MC95">[[Star Wars (1977) 95|''Star Wars'' (1977) 95]]</ref> The [[Hiromi Empire]] also tried to split them from within, using an inside agent [[Hirog]] to create war between two member species, the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]] and the [[Lahsbee/Huhk|Lahsbee]]. This could have caused a civil war if the Alliance members had been forced to take sides, but this also was averted.<ref name="MC94">[[Star Wars (1977) 94|''Star Wars'' (1977) 94]]</ref>

During this same period, the Alliance also had to contend with a [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]]-led coalition of [[Maccabree]] warriors and Imperial loyalists. After a fierce [[Second Battle of Endor|battle over Endor]], resulting in a nominal victory only for the Alliance, they evacuated Endor and once again moved their capital. This conflict, was known as the [[Nagai–Tof War]].<ref name="MC100">[[Star Wars (1977) 100|''Star Wars'' (1977) 100]]</ref> After further encounters with the Nagai at [[Battle of Iskalon (Nagai–Tof War)|Iskalon]] and [[Battle of Trenwyth|Trenwyth]], a confusing [[Battle of Zeltros|battle on Zeltros]] occurred.<ref name="MC102">[[Star Wars (1977) 102|''Star Wars'' (1977) 102]]</ref><ref name="MC103">[[Star Wars (1977) 103|''Star Wars'' (1977) 103]]</ref><ref name="MC104">[[Star Wars (1977) 104|''Star Wars'' (1977) 104]]</ref> The [[Hiromi]], [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]], and the [[Tof/Legends|Tofs]] all separately invaded. In an extraordinary turn of events, the Tofs were repelled by a combined force of Alliance troops, Hiromi, Nagai and their Imperial supporters at the [[Battle of Saijo]].<ref name="MC107">[[Star Wars (1977) 107|''Star Wars'' (1977) 107]]</ref>

